Len was marked M A. Class this morning which means active service, but I don't think he will ever see the Batt. again.
29th. Got our marching orders last night this morning we were up at 2 oclock for we had to catch the early train from Etaps, a big draft went away with us the Camp band played us down to the railway station, it is one of the worst bands as ever I heard, left Etaps in big trucks about 5 o'clock we soon reached Bologne where big batches of Tommies a few Australians got out to go over